    "text": "<p>Ishmail De Niro is an artist, printmaker and artist-curator based between Birmingham and London. His practice moves between screenprint, sculpture and exhibition-making, using industrial processes and reproduced imagery to examine how symbols, materials and architectures carry meaning across time.</p>\n\n<p>Working with fragments of devotional iconography, architectural forms and inherited visual languages, De Niro re-stages historical references through processes of print, repetition and material translation. These works operate between object, image and artefact, exploring how belief, labour and cultural memory are embedded within material culture.</p>\n\n<p>Alongside his studio practice, De Niro develops curatorial projects as social frameworks for gathering and reflection. He is co-founder and co-director of Prayer Room, an artist-led project investigating whether a contemporary art space can also function as an active prayer room and community safe space.</p>\n\n<p>De Niro describes his practice simply as “artist working it out.”</p>",
