    "text": "<div style=\"max-width:860px; margin:0; font-size:16px; line-height:1.55;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 1em 0;\">\n    Prayer Room is an artwork by Ishmail De Niro,\n    collaboratively directed by De Niro, Dinosaur Kilby and Leah Hickey. Founded in Digbeth, Birmingham (2023), Prayer Room operates as an artist-led project space and curatorial platform for Birmingham and beyond. It hosts exhibitions, sober events and public gatherings, and is being developed as a functional <em>multi-faith prayer space</em>.\n    A screen-printed banner reading <em>“No one’s watching, do something”</em> was flown above the space as an ongoing statement and invitation.\n  </p>\n\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 1em 0;\">\n    Prayer Room has presented work by\n    <a href=\"https://www.amarteygolding.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Amartey Golding</a>,\n    <a href=\"http://baesianz.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Baesianz</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://fabianlang.ch/becky-tucker\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Becky Tucker</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://catandeimearmcclay.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Cáit McClay</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://www.campbellmcconnell.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Campbell McConnell</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://catandeimearmcclay.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Éiméar McClay</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://emiialrai.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Emii Alrai</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/powerpuffb1tch/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Fi Sonola</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://joemoss.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Joe Moss</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://poppynash.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Poppy Nash</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://gloamgallery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Rose Hedy Squires</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://partsproject.nl/en/mohammed-shah-jahan-miah-project09/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Shah Jahan</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://www.themoderninstitute.com/artists/sue-tompkins\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Sue Tompkins</a>,\n    <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/umarahmedstudio/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Umar Ahmed</a>\n    and\n    <a href=\"https://ivyvo.site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Ivy Vo</a>, among others.\n    Recent programming includes <em>Peasants Revolt Now!</em> (1 March–19 May 2024), curated by Dinosaur Kilby (<em>key image by</em>\n    <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/iaj.designs/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">iaj.designs</a>);\n    <em>A Mother’s Love</em> (5 July–15 September 2024), curated by Leah Hickey (<em>key image by</em>\n    <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ugly_evil_twin/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">ugly.evil.twin</a>);\n    and <em>If stars ever fell?</em> (6 December 2024–16 March 2025), curated by Ishmail De Niro (<em>key image by</em>\n    <a href=\"https://ivyvo.site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:inherit; text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:0.15em;\">Ivy Vo</a>).\n  </p>\n\n  <p style=\"margin:0;\">\n    Prayer Room has hosted <em>RCA CAP</em>, <em>Tate Liverpool</em>, <em>G39</em> and <em>Spike Island</em> for artist lunches and tours, and has presented film screenings by <em>Falasteen on Film</em>.\n    <em>Graphics and identity</em> for Prayer Room, including exhibition materials across the programme, are by Ishmail De Niro.\n  </p>\n</div>",
